modules.description: This module converts IPv6 addresses to and from Cstruct.t values. It provides functions to parse an IPv6 address from the first 16 bytes of a cstruct, write an IPv6 address into a cstruct, and handle errors either through result types or exceptions. Use cases include network protocol implementations that require direct memory manipulation, such as reading IPv6 addresses from packet data or serializing them for transmission.

This module handles IPv4 address conversions to and from Cstruct buffers. It provides functions to parse an IPv4 address from the first 4 octets of a Cstruct, write an IPv4 address into a Cstruct buffer, and convert an IPv4 address to a newly allocated Cstruct. Use cases include network protocol implementations that require direct memory manipulation, such as packet serialization and deserialization in low-level networking code.

This module provides functions to convert both IPv4 and IPv6 addresses to and from Cstruct.t values, enabling direct manipulation of IP addresses in memory buffers. It supports parsing IP addresses from the beginning of a Cstruct, writing them into Cstruct buffers, and handling conversion errors through result types or exceptions. For example, it can extract an IPv4 address from a packet header or serialize an IPv6 address for network transmission. The main data types are Cstruct.t and the IPv4 and IPv6 address representations.
